    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/duck-masala-with-homemade-nigella-seed-and-chilli-naan-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/duck-masala-with-homemade-nigella-seed-and-chilli-naan-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Roughly chop your<strong> tomato[es]</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>green chilli[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Add your <strong>dried</strong> <strong>yeast</strong> to a large bowl with <strong>120ml</strong><span class=\"text-purple\"> [150ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>and 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, give it a good mix up and set aside for 5-10 min for the yeast to develop</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/duck-masala-with-homemade-nigella-seed-and-chilli-naan-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based,<strong> hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid with a drizzle of your <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> sliced shallot</strong>, <strong>chopped tomato</strong>, <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>ground paprika</strong> and <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>100ml </strong><span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [170ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> to the dish and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/duck-masala-with-homemade-nigella-seed-and-chilli-naan-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, top the curry mixture with your <strong>duck legs </strong>(along with the jelly and fat!) and put the dish in the oven, covered, for 30 min</p><p>After 30 min, remove the dish from the oven, and shred the <strong>duck meat</strong> off the bone, discarding the bone</p><p>Once shredded, stir through <strong>half</strong> the <strong>yoghurt</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) \u2013 this is your <strong>duck masala</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/duck-masala-with-homemade-nigella-seed-and-chilli-naan-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the yeast has developed, add the <strong>pizza base mix</strong>, <strong>sliced chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>nigella seeds </strong>to the bowl with the yeast</p><p>Gradually add up to 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[100ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml] </span><strong>warm water </strong>(you may not need all of it), a little at a time, and gently mix with a plastic spatula until a sticky dough ball has formed</p><p>Tip the dough out onto a<strong> lightly floured </strong>work surface and knead it for 20 secs with <strong>floured hands</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/duck-masala-with-homemade-nigella-seed-and-chilli-naan-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once kneaded, cut your <strong>kneaded</strong> <strong>dough</strong> into 1 ball per person, then roll each <strong>dough ball</strong> out with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> into an oval disc \u2013 these are your<strong> naans</strong></p><p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat and cook each <strong>naan </strong>for 2-3 min on each side or until puffed and golden brown</p><p>Once the naans are cooked through, spread lightly with <strong>butter </strong>and season with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>\u2013 these are your <strong>green chilli & nigella seed naans</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/duck-masala-with-homemade-nigella-seed-and-chilli-naan-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>duck masala </strong>over the<strong> basmati rice </strong>with the <strong>green chilli & nigella seed naans</strong></p><p>Dollop over the <strong>remaining yoghurt</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
